# Implementation Plan - SignalR Real-Time Notifications

We will implement a real-time event distribution network using **ASP.NET Core SignalR** on the backend and **@microsoft/signalr** on the Angular frontend. This replaces the 10-second API polling with immediate push notifications and adds dark/light theme polish to the notification dropdown UI.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. ASP.NET Core Backend Services

#### [NEW] [NotificationHub.cs](file:///d:/shivam/doctor-appointment-system/DoctorAppointmentSystem/DoctorAppointmentSystem/Application/Hubs/NotificationHub.cs)
* Create a SignalR Hub class `NotificationHub : Hub`.
* In `OnConnectedAsync()`, query the `userId` passed in connection parameters and map the Connection ID to a SignalR Group named after the `UserId`.

#### [MODIFY] [Program.cs](file:///d:/shivam/doctor-appointment-system/DoctorAppointmentSystem/DoctorAppointmentSystem/Program.cs)
* Add SignalR services via `builder.Services.AddSignalR()`.
* Configure endpoint mapping: `app.MapHub<NotificationHub>("/notificationHub")`.
* Ensure CORS policies allow credential transmissions (`AllowCredentials()`) for WebSocket Handshakes.

#### [MODIFY] [NotificationService.cs](file:///d:/shivam/doctor-appointment-system/DoctorAppointmentSystem/DoctorAppointmentSystem/Application/Services/NotificationService.cs)
* Inject `IHubContext<NotificationHub>` in the constructor.
* In `CreateNotificationAsync` and `CreateNotificationForRoleAsync`, after saving to the database, push the notification object to the recipient's SignalR group:
  ```csharp
  await _hubContext.Clients.Group(userId.ToString()).SendAsync("ReceiveNotification", notificationDto);
  ```

---

### 2. Angular Frontend Components

#### [MODIFY] [package.json](file:///d:/shivam/doctor-appointment-system/doctor-appointment-frontend/package.json)
* Install `@microsoft/signalr` dependency.

#### [MODIFY] [notification.service.ts](file:///d:/shivam/doctor-appointment-system/doctor-appointment-frontend/src/app/core/services/notification.service.ts)
* Import `HubConnection` and `HubConnectionBuilder` from `@microsoft/signalr`.
* Expose `startConnection(userId: string): void` and `stopConnection(): void`.
* Expose `notificationReceived$` Observable wrapper to listen to push events.

#### [MODIFY] [header.component.ts](file:///d:/shivam/doctor-appointment-system/doctor-appointment-frontend/src/app/shared/components/header/header.component.ts)
* Start the SignalR connection on login/init.
* Subscribe to `notificationReceived$` to prepend fresh notifications instantly.
* Remove the previous 10-second polling interval logic.

#### [MODIFY] [header.component.css](file:///d:/shivam/doctor-appointment-system/doctor-appointment-frontend/src/app/shared/components/header/header.component.css)
* Add and update theme-aware visual rules for the notification bell, unread count badges, and scrollable dropdown.
* Use CSS theme variables (`var(--bg-card)`, `var(--text-primary)`, `var(--border-color)`) so the panel adapts between Light and Dark modes.

